"v.编织 【英】 编结,针织(to make [cloth or a piece of clothing] by looping yarn or thread together with special needles) 【考】 needle : knit / loom : weave(针用来编织/织布机 用来织布)knit : yarn / plait : hair(编织用纱线/编辫用 头发)反义词：ravel (拆开) 【例】 to knit scarves / to knit one's brow when confused v. 编织 【记】源于knot(n 结; v 打结) 【参】knoll(n 小圆丘)这个单词也源于knot. 【类】needle: knit = loom: weave针用来编织 = 织布机用来织布knit: yarn = plait: hair编织用纱线 = 编辫用头发 【反】ravel(v 拆线; 解开) 无 knit (v.)  Old English cnyttan ""to tie with a knot, bind, fasten,"" related to Old Norse knytja ""bind together,"" Middle Low German  knütten ""to tie, knot,"" Old English cnotta ""a knot,"" from Proto-Germanic *knuttjan, from stem *knutt-. Of brows, late 14c. Meaning ""to do knitting"" (especially plain stitch) is from 1520s. Related: Knitted; knitting."
